в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ   Client    в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ    Router   в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ SessionManager  в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ    Store    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   Request   в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ   Server    в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ             в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                              в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ\n                                              в–ј                         в”Ӯ\n                                        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                 в”Ӯ\n                                        в”Ӯ   Workload  в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ\n                                        в”Ӯ   Manager   в”Ӯв—„в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   (if not found)\n                                              в”Ӯ\n                                              в–ј\n                                        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n                                        в”Ӯ  Sandbox    в”Ӯ\n                                        в”Ӯ    Pod      в”Ӯ\n                                        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Configuration\n\n```go\n// Config holds router configuration parameters.\ntype Config struct {\n    // Port is the HTTP server port (default: \"8080\")\n    Port string\n\n    // Debug enables Gin debug mode (default: false)\n    Debug bool\n\n    // EnableTLS enables TLS termination (default: false)\n    EnableTLS bool\n\n    // TLSCert is the path to TLS certificate file\n    TLSCert string\n\n    // TLSKey is the path to TLS key file\n    TLSKey string\n\n    // MaxConcurrentRequests limits concurrent proxy requests (default: 1000)\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n}\n```\n\n### Server State\n\n```go\n// Server represents the HTTP router server.\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    store.Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n}\n```\n\n### Session Management\n\n```go\n// SessionManager defines the interface for session resolution.\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\n// manager implements SessionManager.\ntype manager struct {\n    storeClient     store.Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n}\n\n// SandboxInfo contains information about a resolved sandbox.\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SandboxID   string\n    Name        string\n    Namespace   string\n    SessionID   string\n    Kind        string\n    PodIP       string\n    PodName     string\n    EntryPoints []EntryPoint\n    Status      string\n}\n\n// EntryPoint defines an access point to the sandbox.\ntype EntryPoint struct {\n    Protocol string // \"http\" or \"https\"\n    Endpoint string // host:port\n    Path     string // base path\n}\n\n// CreateSandboxRequest is sent to Workload Manager.\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n}\n\n// CreateSandboxResponse is received from Workload Manager.\ntype CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID   string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    Name        string       `json:\"name\"`\n    Namespace   string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n    EntryPoints []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    Status      string       `json:\"status\"`\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Management\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles JWT signing and key management.\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n\n// JWTClaims represents the JWT payload.\ntype JWTClaims struct {\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n    SessionID string `json:\"session_id,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\n// RouterError represents a router-specific error.\ntype RouterError struct {\n    Code    string\n    Message string\n    Status  int\n}\n\n// Specific error codes\nconst (\n    ErrCodeSessionNotFound       = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrCodeSandboxNotFound       = \"SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrCodeSandboxTemplateNotFound = \"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrCodeJWTSigningFailed      = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n    ErrCodeServerOverloaded      = \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n    ErrCodeSandboxUnreachable    = \"SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE\"\n    ErrCodeSandboxTimeout        = \"SANDBOX_TIMEOUT\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Response | Description |\n|--------|------|----------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` | Liveness probe |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"...\"}` | Readiness probe |\n\n### Invocation Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Headers | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to AgentRuntime |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to CodeInterpreter |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to CodeInterpreter |\n\n### Request Headers\n\n| Header | Required | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | No | Session identifier for existing sessions |\n| `Authorization` | No | Client authentication (forwarded to sandbox) |\n| `Content-Type` | Yes | Request body format |\n\n### Response Headers\n\n| Header | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | Resolved session ID |\n| `X-Forwarded-Host` | Original request host |\n| `X-Forwarded-Proto` | Original request protocol |\n| `X-Forwarded-For` | Client IP chain |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### HTTP Status Code Mapping\n\n| Error Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message | Error Code |\n|-----------------|-------------|---------------|------------|\n| Session not found | 404 | session not found | SESSION_NOT_FOUND |\n| Sandbox template not found | 404 | sandbox template not found | SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND |\n| No entry points | 404 | no entry point found for sandbox | - |\n| JWT signing failure | 500 | failed to sign request | JWT_SIGNING_FAILED |\n| Server overloaded | 429 | server overloaded, please try again later | SERVER_OVERLOADED |\n| Connection refused | 502 | sandbox unreachable | - |\n| Timeout | 504 | sandbox timeout | - |\n| Other proxy errors | 502 | sandbox unreachable | - |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"human-readable message\",\n  \"code\": \"ERROR_CODE\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Session Resolution Errors**: Map store errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n2. **Workload Manager Errors**: Propagate HTTP status codes, map 404 to template not found\n3. **Proxy Errors**: Intercept transport errors and map to 502/504 with user-friendly messages\n4. **JWT Errors**: Return 500 for signing failures, log detailed error\n5. **Store Update Errors**: Log warnings, do not block proxy flow\n\n---\n\n## Algorithms\n\n### Session Resolution Algorithm\n\n```\nfunction GetSandboxBySession(sessionID, namespace, name, kind):\n    if sessionID is empty:\n        return createNewSandbox(namespace, name, kind)\n    \n    sandboxInfo, err := storeClient.GetSession(sessionID)\n    if err == ErrNotFound:\n        return nil, NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)\n    if err != nil:\n        return nil, err\n    \n    return sandboxInfo, nil\n\nfunction createNewSandbox(namespace, name, kind):\n    req := CreateSandboxRequest{Kind: kind, Name: name, Namespace: namespace}\n    resp, err := postToWorkloadManager(req)\n    if err != nil:\n        return nil, err\n    \n    if resp.SessionID == \"\":\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\"sessionId is empty\")\n    \n    sandboxInfo := SandboxInfo{\n        SandboxID:   resp.SandboxID,\n        Name:        resp.Name,\n        SessionID:   resp.SessionID,\n        EntryPoints: resp.EntryPoints,\n    }\n    \n    // Store in cache\n    storeClient.StoreSession(sandboxInfo.SessionID, sandboxInfo)\n    \n    return sandboxInfo, nil\n```\n\n### Upstream URL Resolution\n\n```\nfunction resolveUpstreamURL(sandboxInfo, invocationPath):\n    if len(sandboxInfo.EntryPoints) == 0:\n        return nil, NewNoEntryPointError()\n    \n    // Find matching entry point by path prefix\n    for _, ep := range sandboxInfo.EntryPoints:\n        if strings.HasPrefix(invocationPath, ep.Path):\n            return buildURL(ep, invocationPath), nil\n    }\n    \n    // Fall back to first entry point\n    return buildURL(sandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0], invocationPath), nil\n\nfunction buildURL(entryPoint, path):\n    url := entryPoint.Endpoint\n    if entryPoint.Protocol != \"\" && !strings.Contains(url, \"://\"):\n        url = entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + url\n    }\n    \n    // Normalize path\n    if path != \"\" && !strings.HasPrefix(path, \"/\"):\n        path = \"/\" + path\n    }\n    \n    return url + path\n```\n\n### JWT Generation\n\n```\nfunction GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}):\n    now := time.Now()\n    baseClaims := JWTClaims{\n        RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n            ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(now.Add(jwtExpiration)),\n            IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(now),\n            Issuer:    \"agentcube-router\",\n        },\n    }\n    \n    // Merge custom claims\n    for k, v := range claims:\n        if k == \"session_id\":\n            baseClaims.SessionID = v.(string)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, baseClaims)\n    return token.SignedString(privateKey)\n```\n\n### Concurrency Limiting\n\n```\nfunction concurrencyLimitMiddleware(limit int):\n    semaphore := make(chan struct{}, limit)\n    \n    return func(c *gin.Context):\n        select:\n            case semaphore <- struct{}{}:\n                defer func() { <-semaphore }()\n                c.Next()\n            default:\n                c.AbortWithStatusJSON(429, {\n                    \"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\",\n                    \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n                })\n        }\n    }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Component | Test Cases | Mock Dependencies |\n|-----------|------------|-------------------|\n| Server | Configuration validation, route registration | - |\n| SessionManager | Session resolution, WM integration, error handling | Store, HTTP Client |\n| JWTManager | Token generation, key persistence, signing | K8s Client |\n| Proxy | URL resolution, header forwarding, error mapping | HTTP Transport |\n| Middleware | Concurrency limiting, request ID | - |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Full request flow | Client вҶ’ Router вҶ’ Sandbox with mocked store |\n| Session creation | Missing session ID triggers WM create |\n| Session reuse | Existing session loaded from store |\n| JWT injection | Token generated and attached to proxied request |\n| Health probes | Live and ready endpoints respond correctly |\n| Concurrency limit | Requests rejected when limit exceeded |\n| Error handling | Various error conditions return correct status codes |\n\n### Test Data\n\n```go\n// Example SandboxInfo for tests\nvar testSandboxInfo = &SandboxInfo{\n    SandboxID:   \"sb-12345\",\n    Name:        \"test-agent\",\n    Namespace:   \"default\",\n    SessionID:   \"sess-abc-123\",\n    Kind:        \"AgentRuntime\",\n    PodIP:       \"10.0.0.1\",\n    PodName:     \"test-agent-abc123\",\n    EntryPoints: []EntryPoint{\n        {Protocol: \"http\", Endpoint: \"10.0.0.1:8080\", Path: \"/\"},\n    },\n    Status: \"Running\",\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | - | Workload Manager base URL |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | \"default\" | Namespace for JWT secret |\n\n### CLI Flags\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-port` | \"8080\" | HTTP server port |\n| `-enable-tls` | false | Enable TLS termination |\n| `-tls-cert` | \"\" | TLS certificate file path |\n| `-tls-key` | \"\" | TLS key file path |\n| `-debug` | false | Enable Gin debug mode |\n| `-max-concurrent-requests` | 1000 | Max concurrent requests |\n\n### Default Values\n\n```go\nconst (\n    defaultPort                  = \"8080\"\n    defaultMaxConcurrentRequests = 1000\n    defaultReadTimeout           = 30 * time.Second\n    defaultIdleTimeout           = 90 * time.Second\n    defaultShutdownTimeout       = 10 * time.Second\n    \n    defaultJWTExpiration = 5 * time.Minute\n    defaultRSAKeySize    = 2048\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Direct Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.9+ | HTTP web framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT signing and validation |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Latest | HTTP/2 support |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API client |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API machinery |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n\n### Internal Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Session store interface |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Shared types |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ server.go           # HTTP server setup, Gin engine, route registration\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ proxy.go            # Reverse proxy implementation with httputil\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ session_manager.go  # Session resolution and sandbox lookup\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ jwt.go              # JWT generation, signing, key management\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ config.go           # Configuration types and constants\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ handlers.go         # HTTP handler functions\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ middleware.go       # Concurrency limiting and custom middleware\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ health.go           # Health check handlers\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ errors.go           # Error types and codes\nв””в”Җв”Җ doc.go              # Package documentation\n\ncmd/router/\nв””в”Җв”Җ main.go             # Entry point, CLI flags, server lifecycle\n```\n\n---\n\n## Constants Reference\n\n| Name | Value | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| `LastActivityAnnotationKey` | `\"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"` | Annotation key for last activity |\n| `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key size for JWT signing |\n| `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | JWT token expiration |\n| `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes secret name for JWT keys |\n| `PrivateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n| `PublicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **HTTP/2 Support**: The Router uses h2c (HTTP/2 without TLS) for internal communication, enabling efficient multiplexing of requests to sandbox pods.\n\n2. **JWT Key Persistence**: RSA keys are stored in Kubernetes secrets to ensure pod restart resilience. When not running in-cluster, ephemeral keys are generated.\n\n3. **Session Creation Delegation**: Creating new sandboxes is delegated to the Workload Manager to avoid duplicating orchestration logic.\n\n4. **Connection Pooling**: A shared `http.Transport` is used for connection pooling and reuse when proxying to sandboxes.\n\n5. **WebSocket Support**: WebSocket upgrade is supported via reverse proxy passthrough.\n\n6. **Best-Effort Activity Tracking**: Last-activity updates are logged as warnings on failure but do not block the proxy flow.\n\n7. **Path Normalization**: The Director ensures all outbound paths start with `/` for consistent routing.\n\n---\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Delta Specification](delta-spec.md) - Detailed requirements and scenarios\n- [Client-Go Library](../../deployment/client-go.md) - Kubernetes client usage\n- [Session Routing Design](../../session-routing/design.md) - High-level routing design\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/common_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types/request.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types/response.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":24,"character":6},"end":{"line":24,"character":17}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":45,"character":20},"end":{"line":45,"character":31}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":75,"character":6},"end":{"line":75,"character":17}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":78,"character":8},"end":{"line":78,"character":19}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775858080132,"end":1775858080163}}}}
