{"type":"text","timestamp":1775858102216,"sessionID":"ses_2869f70cdffe6GHqTShtbr9109","part":{"id":"prt_d796402670013E5P3mnmz3MEEY","messageID":"msg_d7963d9e3001feiAgsoKeyCx2P","sessionID":"ses_2869f70cdffe6GHqTShtbr9109","type":"text","text":"I've written the design.md file for AR-009 - Router HTTP еҸҚеҗ‘д»ЈзҗҶж ёеҝғ. The document includes:\n\n**Key Sections:**\n1. **Overview** - Purpose and key responsibilities of the Router\n2. **Architecture** - High-level design with ASCII diagrams showing component interactions\n3. **Data Structures** - Go types for Config, Server, SessionManager, JWTManager, and errors\n4. **API Contracts** - REST endpoints (health checks, invocation routes) and headers\n5. **Error Handling** - HTTP status code mapping and error response format\n6. **Algorithms** - Pseudocode for session resolution, URL resolution, JWT generation, and concurrency limiting\n7. **Testing Strategy** - Unit test coverage and integration test scenarios\n8. **Configuration** - Environment variables, CLI flags, and default values\n9. **Dependencies** - Direct (gin, jwt, k8s client-go) and internal dependencies\n10. **File Structure** - Package layout under `pkg/router/` and `cmd/router/`\n11. **Constants** - Key constants like JWT expiration, key sizes, secret names\n\nThe design is located at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-009/design.md` and follows the patterns established in other AR documents (AR-006, AR-007, etc.).","time":{"start":1775858102213,"end":1775858102213}}}
